{0 Rename refactoring}

Rename a note, heading, block ID, or explicit attribute anchor and update every
vault link or embed that resolves to it.

{1 Input}

The [textDocument/rename] request supplies a cursor position and a non-empty
new name. The cursor may be on the definition or on a resolved link to it.

{1 Result}

The server returns a [WorkspaceEdit] containing edits for the definition and
all references. Edits replace only the semantic destination component: link
labels, wikilink aliases, embed markers, and other fragments are preserved.

Renaming a note updates its link destinations and includes an LSP file rename;
the file remains in its existing directory. Heading definitions replace the heading text. Heading link fragments use the
new heading text; resolution subsequently uses its slug. Block and attribute
definitions replace only their identifier, without the [^] or [#] marker.

Results are grouped by document and ordered by byte position.

{1 Safety}

No edit is returned when the cursor has no resolved rename target, the new
name is empty, or an identifier contains characters outside letters, digits,
[-], and [_]. Note names may not contain path separators or be [.] or [..].
